      "role": "user",
      "content": "You keep using words like \"vital,\" \"necessary,\" and \"fair trade-off.\" It feels like you're saying the loss of these coal jobs and the impact on those towns is just an inevitable cost that we have to accept. \n\nAre there any actual arguments to be made that this bill might be bad for the state in the long run? Like, from an economic or stability standpoint? I want to know if there's a legitimate perspective that says we shouldn't be doing this right now.",
